00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,500
Submitting Relief Requests in DRIMS

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Click DRIMS in the sidebar, then select Requests

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,500
View the list of all requests

4
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,800
Click the New button to create a request

5
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,300
Select the disaster incident you are responding to

6
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,800
Choose the destination area and set the priority level

7
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:27,300
Set the date supplies are needed and explain why

8
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,300
Enter the number of people who will receive supplies

9
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,800
Click Add a line to request specific items

10
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,800
Select the product and enter the quantity needed

11
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,800
Click Save to save your request as a draft

12
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:47,600
Click Submit to send the request for approval

13
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,600
The request is now pending approval

14
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,100
Tutorial complete!

